gm recall-store discipline (present-tense rule): gm's default-namespace rs-learn store holds gm/rs-* method, tooling, and invariants ONLY. Never memorize specifics of a project gm is merely used ON -- its file paths, line numbers, .gm/prd.yml or mutables.yml contents, app/shader/UI internals, or version numbers -- into gm's store; that pollutes every gm session's recall with foreign context. A finding ABOUT a target project belongs in THAT project's own .gm store. When a lesson surfaces while gm drives another repo, memorize only the generalizable gm-method lesson, scrubbed of the project's names/paths/state. This binds the mutable-resolve/prd-resolve auto-memo (witness_evidence is durable recall -- witness in gm-method terms). A code-side classifier reject was judged too brittle (false-rejects legit gm memos citing .gm/prd.yml mechanisms); discipline + on-sight memorize-prune of foreign-specific memos is the enforcement.